{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3564529,"name":"Prince","username":"Prince","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/ba9def/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-21T15:40:54.804Z","cooked":"<p>Currency we have a button that our driver has to press at the start of each match to reset our gyro. The robot has to be straight during this time so we can zero our heading. I’ve seen a lot of teams not do this. How can we accomplish this. We use <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span> swerve code</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-21T15:40:54.804Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":17,"reads":59,"readers_count":58,"score":96.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":496449,"topic_slug":"setting-heading-for-sweve","display_username":"Prince","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57204,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1792 Lead Programmer"},"post_url":"/t/setting-heading-for-sweve/496449/1","custom_user_title":"1792 Lead Programmer","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3564537,"name":"Tim Winters","username":"ArchdukeTim","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/archduketim/{size}/256125_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-21T15:47:06.731Z","cooked":"<p>A lot of teams have a vision pipeline that is using the April tags to provide information about robot location to their software. Part of this info is the angle that the robot is facing. As long as the cameras can see the tag, the <em>estimated pose</em> will be updated to reflect this calculated rotation value. This works as long as you have very good measurements of how your cameras are positioned relative to your robot.</p>
<p>For teams that don’t have vision, they may be resetting their heading at the beginning of auto based on their auto path’s starting configuration. This is less reliable, since the robot doesn’t actually know if the heading of the robot matches what it is set to in their auto, but if it’s close enough then the drivers might not notice slight error.</p>
<p>You can get similar behavior by manually resetting your heading based on some known value. Most if not all gyros will start with a heading of zero, so some teams choose to turn their robot on with the front of their robot facing away from the blue alliance wall (since this is 0º in WPILib’s coordinate system). Other teams will just place their robot for auto in the same orientation each time and when auto starts, reset their gyro to this predefined value (similar to it using the auto path, but less versatile).</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-21T15:47:44.761Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":16.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":496449,"topic_slug":"setting-heading-for-sweve","display_username":"Tim Winters","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":19820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"78 AIR Strike Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/setting-heading-for-sweve/496449/2","custom_user_title":"78 AIR Strike Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3564543,"name":"Kade Rabe","username":"Kadd","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/kadd/{size}/178400_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-21T15:53:19.036Z","cooked":"<p>the main options are:</p>
